race.comment: CORONATION DAY (8) hit the ground running last start and was never headed (23.61) at this track in Grade 4 over 407m. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Looks to have an edge on most of these. LISSY'S GEM (1) has been hard to follow lately, running fourth (24.40) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at this track. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. BLACKJACK BOB (7) stalked lead from an outside box last start before finishing third (24.39) at this track in a Grade 4 over 407m. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Leading chance. VELOCITY KIRRILY (2) is likely to have admirers. Something for the Multiples: FEISTY FAWNY (4)
